Class 07
Handeling multiple windows
In order to handle multiple windows we will be using:
getWindowHandle()=gives you the unike Id for that tab window own unique adress
getWindowHandles()

Window Handle:
is a unique ID that holds the address of the window or a tab
Its is approximately 40 alphanumeric character ID

Syncronization
-is a process of bringing the speed of two or more components to the same level
in this case we are bringing our script and page load to the same speed level

Thread.sleep()- it's a static wait it's not going to change according to the element or the page load
its  a static wait/unconditional wait

Types of selenium:
Implicit wait=its a global wait tells selenium to wait a certain amount of time throughout the program
R. it tells the webdriver to wait for a certain amount of time before throwing an exception.It's usually set to 20 sec works with findElement method
(if element found in less secounds the rest of the time set will be ignored but if not found within the time set will throw an exeption Error)
Implicit wait is usually set to 20 sec. if your element is found in any time between the remaining time that time will be ignored and your script
will move on to the line or action.If element is not found in a given time, Only then you will get exemption(DOES NOT WORK WITH FINDELEMENTS or list)
only works with FindElement.

